[var(--color-border)]\\\",\\\"aria-labelledby\\\":\\\"design-heading\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"kvrn-container max-w-3xl\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"kvrn-label mb-12\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"design-heading\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Design logic\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"space-y-12\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"Why no drawstring?\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[2fr_3fr] gap-6 md:gap-12 pb-12 border-b border-[var(--color-border)] last:border-0 last:pb-0\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[15px] font-light\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Why no drawstring?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[14px] font-light text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"A drawstring exists because the hood structure is insufficient to maintain its form independently. We built a hood structure — three separate panels seamed to create a self-supporting dome — that does not require external support. The drawstring is therefore unnecessary. Its absence is a consequence of solving the problem correctly.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"Why interior zippers?\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[2fr_3fr] gap-6 md:gap-12 pb-12 border-b border-[var(--color-border)] last:border-0 last:pb-0\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[15px] font-light\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Why interior zippers?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[14px] font-light text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"A standard kangaroo pocket holds items that move freely and can fall. An interior zipper pocket holds items that stay. The zipper runs parallel to the pocket opening — invisible from outside, accessible from inside. Both sides. It costs more to produce. It is worth it.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"Why no visible branding?\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[2fr_3fr] gap-6 md:gap-12 pb-12 border-b border-[var(--color-border)] last:border-0 last:pb-0\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[15px] font-light\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Why no visible branding?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[14px] font-light text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Visible branding on a garment performs a function: it communicates that the person wearing it values the label more than the object. KVRN is designed for the opposite — for the person who wants the best version of the thing, not the loudest version of the name. One rubber patch on the hood. Nothing else needs to be said.\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",\\\"Why 400 GSM when 300 is sufficient?\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-[2fr_3fr] gap-6 md:gap-12 pb-12 border-b border-[var(--color-border)] last:border-0 last:pb-0\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[15px] font-light\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Why 400 GSM when 300 is sufficient?\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-[14px] font-light text-[var(--color-muted)] leading-relaxed\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"At 300 GSM, a hoodie is functional. At 400 GSM+, it becomes structural — it holds its shape, drapes rather than hangs, and maintains its weight and presence after years of wear. The difference is perceptible immediately. There is no argument for the lesser weight.\\\"}]]}]]}]]}]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"19:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"section-y border-b border-[var(--color-border)] bg-[var(--color-bg-dark)] text-[var(--color-text-on-dark)]\\\",\\\"aria-labelledby\\\":\\\"position-heading\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"kvrn-container\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"